The paper deals with the problem of finding a set with maximum cohesion in an undirected network, which is a common problem in social and complex networks. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves optimization and maximizing a certain metric.
